  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving agricultural production and incomes for 10,000 smallholder farmers in Ghana and Mozambique benefiting 50,000 people.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project, supported by DFID&#x2019;s UK Aid Match, aims to increase yields, productivity and incomes of 10,000 smallholder farms in Ghana and Mozambique through access to finance, savings, insurance, financial education and extension services. Access to tailored financial services, training in modern agricultural techniques and improved linkages to markets will enable the farmers to improve their livelihoods. In addition there will be 40,000 indirect beneficiaries (based on an average household size of 5). These family dependents will benefit from increased access to good nutrition, education, health care and improved housing.</narrative>
  </description>
